is catalog includes binary\nsystems with significantly asymmetric mass ratios, which had not been observed\nin data taken before April 2019. We also find that 11 of the 39 events detected\nsince April 2019 have positive effective inspiral spins under our default prior\n(at 90% credibility), while none exhibit negative effective inspiral spin.\nGiven the increased sensitivity of Advanced LIGO and Advanced Virgo, the\ndetection of 39 candidate events in ~26 weeks of data (~1.5 per week) is\nconsistent with GWTC-1.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2020 18:01:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 26 Feb 2021 16:31:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 8 Mar 2021 18:36:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-15"}
{"id":"2010.14528","submitter":"Alejandro Jim\\'enez-Cano","authors":"Alejandro Jim\\'enez-Cano and Yuri N. Obukhov","title":"Gravitational waves in metric-affine gravity theory","comments":"21 pages, no figures, no tables. Minor changes. arXiv admin note:\n  text overlap with arXiv:1702.05185","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. D 103, 024018 (2021)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.103.024018","report-no":null,"categories":"gr-qc hep-th","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We derive the exact gravitational wave solutions in a general class of\nquadratic metric-affine gauge gravity models. The Lagrangian includes all\npossible linear and quadratic invariants constructed from the torsion,\nnonmetricity and the curvature. The ansatz for the gravitational wave\nconfiguration and the properties of the wave solutions are patterned following\nthe corresponding ansatz and the properties of the plane-fronted\nelectromagnetic wave.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2020 18:01:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Jan 2021 16:17:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-14"}
