{"id":"2010.16257","submitter":"Wei Zhan","authors":"Wei Zhan","title":"Universality for Doubly Stochastic Matrices","comments":"16 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.FA math.GN math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that the set of entries generated by any finite set of doubly\nstochastic matrices is nowhere dense, in contrast to the cases of stochastic\nmatrices or unitary matrices. In other words, there is no finite universal set\nof doubly stochastic matrices, even with the weakest notion of universality.\n  Our proof is based on a theorem for topological semigroups with the\nconvergent property. A topological semigroup is convergent if every infinite\nproduct converges. We show that in a compact and convergent semigroup, under\nsome restrictions, the closure of every finitely generated subsemigroup can be\ninstead generated directly by the generating set and the limits of infinite\nproducts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Oct 2020 00:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Apr 2021 01:00:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-02"}
